OL,3,CClosing Torquay custody centre would
OL,4,Chit 'most vulnerable', say lawyers
OL,6,F"This includes the potential pilot
OL,7,Fclosure of Torquay custody and the
OL,8,Ftemporary redeployment of staff. A
OL,9,Ffinal decision has yet to be made,
OL,10,Fwith proposals being discussed and
OL,11,Fcarefully considered in force this
OL,12,Fweek and the Police and Crime
OL,13,FCommissioner will be kept fully
OL,14,Finformed of our plans.
OL,16,F"It is vital that we improve the
OL,17,Fcapacity, resilience and operating
OL,18,Fenvironment of our custody estate.
OL,26,@xD@AOU
