OL,3,CClosing Torquay custody centre would
OL,4,Chit 'most vulnerable', say lawyers
OL,6,F"Our current provision across Devon
OL,7,Fand Cornwall (Camborne, Newquay,
OL,8,FPlymouth, Torquay, Exeter and
OL,9,FBarnstaple) presents strategic and
OL,10,Foperational challenges creating
OL,11,Fwelfare, health and safety risks for
OL,12,Fdetainees and staff.
OL,14,F"Operating costs exceed budgets, and
OL,15,Ffurther costly improvements are needed
OL,16,Fto bring some custody suites up to
OL,17,Fsafety compliance.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/9
